steps.prompt:
Draft consent appointment scheduling emails for clinical trial candidates approved by the investigator.

Trial: {{trial_name}} (Protocol: {{protocol_id}})
Site: {{site_id}} | Investigator: {{investigator_id}}
Investigator decisions from EDC: {{steps.receive-investigator-decisions.output}}
Original eligible candidates: {{steps.screen-eligibility.output.eligible_candidates}}

For each candidate that the investigator has approved for contact, draft a personalized scheduling email. Each email must: (1) introduce the trial by name and briefly explain the purpose in plain language (2-3 sentences, no jargon); (2) explain that participation is voluntary and they can ask any questions; (3) propose 2-3 appointment time slots for the initial informed consent visit; (4) provide site contact information and the investigator's name; (5) include a clear subject line referencing the trial name.

Format each email with a header block: --- PATIENT: [patient_initials] | SUBJECT: [subject line] --- followed by the email body. Do not include real patient names or identifiers beyond initials.
